Olaide Oyelude, Katsina A Katsina Senior Magistrates’ Court has ordered that one Abubakar Bello, 35, be remanded in prison custody till October 8, 2019, for allegedly sodomising the 15 year-old-son of his neighbour. The presiding Senior Magistrate of the court, Hajiya Fadile Dikko, gave the order on Tuesday following a request by the police prosecutor in charge of the case, Sergeant Lawal Bello. According to him, the accused, who resides in Daudawa village in the Faskari Local Government Area of the state, allegedly lured his victim to a valley near a river at the Hayin Kado village and proceeded to have an unlawful and unnatural anal sex with the victim. The victim’s father, Hassan Adamu, who became aware of the incident, reported the matter to the Faskari Divisional Police Headquarters on August 8, 2019. Abubakar was subsequently arrested and charged for the offence, which contravened provisions of Section 284 of the Penal Code. READ ALSO: ICPC seeks forfeiture of NDDC director’s petrol station The police prosecutor asked the court for additional time to conclude investigation into the case. The court granted the request and ordered that the accused be remanded in prison until the next adjourned date. Copyright PUNCH.
